OL,4,CThe town living in the shadow of
OL,5,CIndia-China war
OL,6, Thutan Chewang, 71, still remembers the
OL,7, day the war began.
OL,9,FIt was October 1962 and China had just
OL,10,Flaunched a surprise attack on what was
OL,11,Fthen known as the North East Frontier
OL,12,FAgency (which later became Arunachal
OL,13,FPradesh state) in north-eastern India.
OL,15,F"They (Chinese troops) came charging
OL,16,Ffrom all sides. People started to flee,
OL,17,Ffearing for their lives," says Mr
OL,18,FChewang, who was just 11 at the time.
